      <p class="pf-sub">Installing a new boiler on a contaminated system is one of the most common reasons manufacturers reject warranty claims.</p>
      <div class="pf-card pf-card-orange" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h3 style="text-align:center;">Why a Power Flush Before Your New Boiler Matters</h3>
        <p>All major boiler manufacturers including <a href="https://www.worcester-bosch.co.uk/professionals/support/technical-support" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Worcester Bosch</a> and <a href="https://www.vaillant.co.uk/for-installers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vaillant</a> require a clean system as a warranty condition. Sludge and magnetite from your old system can damage the new heat exchanger within months if not removed first. Under <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/boiler-plus" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boiler Plus regulations</a>, installers must also confirm the system is clean and efficient at the point of installation.</p>
        <p>We carry out the power flush before the new boiler is connected, not after. This protects the heat exchanger from day one and keeps your warranty intact. A power flush costs from £350 and is available as a bundle with your new boiler at a better combined price. Ask when you call to book your survey.</p>
