        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">SIZE</span>&nbsp; What size boiler do I need for my Liverpool home?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Boiler output is measured in kilowatts. A 1 to 2 bed Liverpool property typically needs a 24 to 28kW combi boiler. A 3-bed semi needs 28 to 32kW. Larger properties with multiple bathrooms need 32 to 40kW or a system boiler. Older Liverpool properties with gravity-fed systems often require a regular boiler. We calculate the correct size at the free survey based on your property, number of radiators and hot water demand. Fitting an incorrectly sized boiler is one of the most common and costly installation mistakes.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">LIVERPOOL</span>&nbsp; Are there complications with older Liverpool properties?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Liverpool has one of the highest concentrations of Victorian and Edwardian housing in England. Many have gravity-fed systems, back boilers, chimneys used as flue routes and non-standard pipework that differs significantly from modern builds. Our engineers have 30 years experience in Liverpool's specific housing stock and know what to anticipate before they open a wall. The free survey is essential for any older Liverpool property.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">TIME</span>&nbsp; How long does a boiler installation take?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A straightforward like-for-like combi boiler replacement typically takes 4 to 6 hours and is completed in a single day. More complex installations take 1 to 3 days. Same-day and next-day installation is available for emergency replacements across Liverpool. We confirm the expected duration at the free survey.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">WARRANTY</span>&nbsp; What warranty do I get with a new boiler?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Worcester Bosch and Vaillant offer up to 10-year manufacturer warranties when installed by an accredited installer and serviced annually. Ideal and Baxi offer between 5 and 10 years depending on the model. All our installations carry a 12-month workmanship guarantee. We issue the Benchmark certificate and register the warranty with the manufacturer on installation day. Annual servicing is required to keep the warranty valid.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">FLUSH</span>&nbsp; Do I need a power flush before my new boiler?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>In most cases yes, particularly if your system is more than 5 years old. All major manufacturers require a clean system as a warranty condition. We carry out the power flush before connecting the new boiler to protect the heat exchanger from day one. A power flush costs from £350 and is available as a bundle with your new boiler at a better combined price.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">GRANTS</span>&nbsp; Is there a grant for a new boiler in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Liverpool homeowners on qualifying benefits including Universal Credit and Pension Credit may be eligible for the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/apply-great-british-insulation-scheme" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ECO4 scheme</a> which can fund a full boiler replacement. The <a href="https://www.gov.uk/apply-boiler-upgrade-scheme" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boiler Upgrade Scheme</a> provides grants of up to £7,500 towards heat pump installation. We assess your eligibility at the free survey at no cost.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Ideal Plumbing Solutions is Gas Safe registered. Verify our registration at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. All installations are carried out by our own directly employed engineers. We never use sub-contractors. A Gas Safe registered engineer is a legal requirement for all domestic gas work in the UK.</p></div></details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

